{"questionId":"13709","questionHtml":"<p>A particle moves along a horizontal line such that at time <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> seconds, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> ≥ 0, its acceleration <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> = 2<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> − 1. When <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> = 6 , its displacement <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n</math></span> from a fixed origin O is 18.25 m.&nbsp;When <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> = 15, its displacement from O is 922.75 m. Find an expression for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n</math></span> in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>attempt to integrate <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> to find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v = \\int {a\\,{\\text{d}}t = \\int {\\left( {2t - 1} \\right)} } \\,{\\text{d}}t\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>a</mi>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>=</mo>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = {t^2} - t + c\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s = \\int {v\\,{\\text{d}}t = \\int {\\left( {{t^2} - t + c} \\right)} } \\,{\\text{d}}t\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>=</mo>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{{t^3}}}{3} - \\frac{{{t^2}}}{2} + ct + d\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt at substitution of given values&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 6{\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\,18.25 = 72 - 18 + 6c + d\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>18.25</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>72</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>18</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 15{\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\,922.75 = 1125 - 112.5 + 15c + d\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>15</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>922.75</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1125</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>112.5</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>15</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>solve simultaneously:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c =&nbsp; - 6{\\text{,}}\\,\\,d = 0.25\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.25</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow s = \\frac{{{t^3}}}{3} - \\frac{{{t^2}}}{2} +&nbsp; - 6t + \\frac{1}{4}\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>s</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13709","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_6","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A particle moves along a horizontal line such that at time t seconds, t ≥ 0, its acceleration a is given by a = 2 t − 1. When t = 6 , its displacement s from a fixed origin O is 18","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"H_6","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.13—Kinematic problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}